data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. Built to perfection with the most incredible one-story layout ever! Look forward to seeing spaces that provide privacy and serenity as well as spaces to congregate and enjoy others. The great room invites all---friends and residents----to come together. Sit at the kitchen counter, read the paper at the nearby dining room table, or watch TV in the wonderful lounge/TV area. This spacious great room is at the heart of this home. It enjoys a lanai and view of the large corner lot and partial conservation view. Four bedrooms are found in three separate areas. At the front of the home, two bedrooms, a bathroom, and a retreat space create a unique and enviable suite. To the right side of the home, opposite the great room, and entered through its own hallway, there is a large bedroom with an ensuite bathroom. At the back right of the home and entered from the great room is the owner’s luxury suite---bedroom, massive walk-in closet, and luxury bathroom. Also unique to the owner’s retreat is a hallway on the backside of the great room wall where the TV is. Access this corridor through the far side of the great room and through another opening on the other side of the great room TV wall. A full bank of storage closets on one side and a powder room for guests on the other side are in this corridor. Also found here is a private study. What an ideal space for working from home! Lastly there is a large inside utility room, 3 car garage with extra space including access to an above garage floored attic. An extensive list of upgrades to the base home (including smart home features) is online (Ask your realtor for the list or see it when you visit the home). However, in addition to those features, the owners included the other upgrades listed below. This David Weekley home located in one of the Tampa Bay area’s best communities, Bexley. Not only are you buying a well-constructed home with transferable warranties, but you are also buying a lifestyle. The Bexley community includes 7 parks, miles of trails for walking and running, fit stations, dog parks, playgrounds, a full-service café, the Bexley Club, and the Hub—a new commercial area with restaurants, retailers and services. A pamphlet on the community is attached online in MLX. Just off highway 54, Bexley is near roadways to Tampa Airport, Downtown Tampa, and Westly Chapel. Be sure to drive this wonderful area to find out what your future holds.
